==2008== The William & Mary Tribe football team represented the [[College of William & Mary]] in [[National Collegiate Athletic Association]] (NCAA) [[Division I (NCAA)|Division I]] [[Division I (NCAA)#Football Championship Subdivision|Football Championship Subdivision]] (FCS) [[college football]] during the [[2008 NCAA Division I FCS football season|2009 season]]. William & Mary competed as a member of the [[Colonial Athletic Association]] (CAA) under head football coach [[Jimmye Laycock]] and played their home games at [[Zable Stadium]]. The 2008 campaign came on the heels of a 4â7 record in 2007. William & Mary finished the season ranked #20 according to the final Sports Network FCS Poll.
The 2008 season was also the final one for redshirt senior cornerback and punt returner [[Derek Cox]]. Cox, an All-Conference player, would later be selected in the [[2009 NFL Draft]] by the [[Jacksonville Jaguars]] with the 9th pick in the 3rd round (73rd overall), making him the second-highest player ever drafted out of William & Mary ([[Darren Sharper]], 60th overall pick in the 2nd round, [[1997 NFL Draft|1997]]). {{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=2008 |Team= William & Mary Tribe |Image= New William & Mary Logo.gif |ImageSize=130 |Conference= Colonial Athletic Association |Division= South |ShortConference= CAA |Record= 7â4 |ConfRecord= 5â3 |TSNRank= 20<ref>[http://www.sportsnetwork.com/merge/tsnform.aspx?c=sportsnetwork&page=cfoot2/misc/2008_poll.htm Sports Network's FCS College Football Poll]</ref> |HeadCoach= [[Jimmye Laycock]] (29th year) |OffCoach= [[Zbig Kepa]] (16th year) |DefCoach= [[Bob Shoop]] (2nd year) |OScheme= |DScheme= |StadiumArena= [[Zable Stadium]]&nbsp;(12,259 cap.) |Champion= |BowlTourney= |BowlTourneyResult= }} {{CFB Schedule Start|time=|rank=|ranklink=no|rankyear=2008|tv=|attend=yes}} {{CFB Schedule Entry | date = September 6 | time = 6:00 pm | w/l = l | nonconf = yes | away = yes | neutral = | rank = | opponent = [[2008 NC State Wolfpack football team|N.C. State]] | opprank = | site_stadium = [[Carter-Finley Stadium]] | site_cityst = [[Raleigh, North Carolina|Raleigh, NC]] | gamename = | score = 24â34 | overtime = | tv = | attend = 56,694 }} {{CFB Schedule Entry | date = September 13 | time = 7:05 pm | w/l = w | nonconf = yes | away = | neutral = | rank = | opponent = {{cfb link|year=2008|team=VMI Keydets|title=Virginia Military Institute}} | opprank = | site_stadium = [[Zable Stadium]] | site_cityst = [[Williamsburg, Virginia|Williamsburg, VA]] | gamename = | score = 52â17 | overtime = | tv = | attend = 10,624 }} {{CFB Schedule Entry | date = September 20 | time = 7:00 pm | w/l = w | nonconf = yes | away = | neutral = | rank = | oppon